<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                        <head>523. Telegram 1730 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d523fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/3–756. Secret;
                                Priority; Limit Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-07">March 7, 1956, 6:25
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d523-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d523-1"/>
                        <p>1730. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Medical case history Liu Yung-ming received from Missouri State Hospital
                            No. 4. It is being forwarded promptly to American Red Cross for
                            transmittal to Red Cross in Peiping. You may inform <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> to this effect at tomorrow’s
                            meeting.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HH_1"><hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>